cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or paper, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Mnemonic State Graph (MSG): A Cue-Gated, Human-in-the-Loop Memory Architecture for Conversational AI Systems"
abstract: "MSG is a memory architecture built on the thesis that cognition in a human-LLM system is distributed. It combines a dual-graph working memory (dependency DAG + association graph), a confidence model that decays only on ignored cues, a six-type cue taxonomy with differentiated acceptance dynamics, and a Socratic conflict-resolution protocol. Evaluated across 132 randomized world instances, MSG achieves +22.8 pp accuracy over naive RAG at 4.8x lower token cost."
